headline: 3 Healthcare Stocks Skating on Thin Ice
summary: From novel pharmaceuticals to telemedicine, most healthcare companies are on a mission to drive better patient outcomes. But speed bumps such as inventory destockings have persisted in the wake of COVID-19, and over the past six months, the industry has pulled back by 3.5%. This performance was disheartening since the S&P 500 gained 4.5%.
